Harmony Gold Retraces Losses After Upgrading Wafi-Golpu Project Resources

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-07-20T11:22:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/harmony-gold-retraces-losses-after-upgrading-wafi-golpu-project-resources.html
Harmony Gold Mining Co. shares
retraced earlier losses in Johannesburg trading after the
company upgraded the resource estimate for its Wafi-Golpu
project in  Papua New Guinea .  Shares in the company rose 0.4 percent to 98.11 rand as of
1:18 p.m. local time, having earlier fallen as much as 1.6
percent.  The resource of gold and copper increased by 57 percent to
over 1 billion metric tons, Harmony said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  